Creating a new VM using KVM qcow2 wiht RHEL 10 ISO image. 

-- Select the Disk space, CPU and Memory to allocate. 
-- Start the machine for manual install of RHEL. 
----Inside the New VM-----
- Select the Language and Support: US
- Connect to RedHat if required. 
- KDUMP: Keep it On, it store kernel crash it will capture information from the system 
	to analyze the reason behind the system crash. 
- Software Selection: Depending on your Usage. Keep it GUI for beginner.
- Root Account*: Ensure to create a root account beforehand to avoid any 
	issue after the RHEL is boot up.
- User Account*: If you wish you can add a user with root privalages. Also, can 
		modified the Grooup and user ID for this user. 

